Related content

   Symbolbild - Ehrenmord - Pakistan

Violence against women on the rise in Pakistan 23.09.2019

   Pakistan ranks as the sixth most dangerous country in the world for
   women, with cases of sexual crimes and domestic violence recording a
   rapid rise. Activists blame society's patriarchal attitudes for the
   problem.
   Häusliche Gewalt gegen Frauen Symbolfoto

Inside Europe: France targets femicide and domestic violence 06.09.2019

   France declared war on domestic violence during the week, with the
   government announcing a series of measures specifically targeted
   against the killing of women, and launched a two-month forum on the
   subject. The country has among Europe's highest rates of so-called
   femicides. But from Paris, Lisa Bryant reports activists say much more
   needs to be done — both in France and in Europe.
   Jemen Frau mit ihrem Baby

Empowering women in Yemen's civil war 25.09.2019

   When it comes to gender equality, Yemen is ranked worst in the world,
   and women and girls have suffered massively in the country's five years
   of fighting. Yet CARE gender activist Suha Basharen sees glimmers of
   hope.
