Inside Europe: France targets femicide and domestic violence 06.09.2019

   France declared war on domestic violence during the week, with the
   government announcing a series of measures specifically targeted
   against the killing of women, and launched a two-month forum on the
   subject. The country has among Europe's highest rates of so-called
   femicides. But from Paris, Lisa Bryant reports activists say much more
   needs to be done — both in France and in Europe.
