   of President Donald Trump.   Go to article

Germany's Heiko Maas pushes multilateralism at UN 4h ago

   USA UN-Generalversammlung Heiko Maas (Getty Images/AFP/J. Eisele)

   Working together is "not a betrayal" and shows love for one's own
   country, top diplomat Heiko Maas said at the UN General Assembly,
   contradicting US President Trump's anti-globalist speech days before,
   albeit indirectly.

Ex-French President Jacques Chirac dies, aged 86 3h ago

   Jacques Chirac (Imago/IP3press)

   The former French president, Jacques Chirac, has died "peacefully" at
   the age of 86, his family said. The conservative politician led France
   between 1995 and 2007.

Austria's Strache probed over misuse of party funds 4h ago

   Heinz-Christian Strache (picture-alliance/picturedesk/G. Artinger)

   Prosecutors have confirmed an investigation against the ex-leader of
   far-right FPÖ party, Heinz-Christian Strache, on suspicion of
   embezzling party funds. Strache was forced out of government over the
   "Ibiza" scandal.

US-Japan mini trade deal shows Trump is running out of time 4h ago

   US President Donald Trump

   The "minideal" is a rare compromise by the US president, who has
   displayed a penchant for launching trade wars in pursuit of
   comprehensive trade deals. What's prompting Donald Trump to back down
   from his hawkish stance?

HK's Lam meets public for 'dialogue' 3h ago

   Hong Kong leader Carrie Lam

   Carrie Lam has spoken with members of the Hong Kong public in a special
   dialogue session to resolve the city's political unrest. The meeting
   comes after 17 straight weeks of sometimes violent anti-government
   protests.

Johnson dares opposition to call snap election 20h ago

   UK Prime Minister Boris Johnson

   The prime minister challenged the opposition to vote no-confidence in
   the government. Members of parliament were meeting for the first time
   in two weeks following an "unlawful" suspension of parliament ruling.

ISS should orbit forever, Roscosmos chief says 6m ago

   Italian Astronaut Luca Parmitano plays a DJ set from the ISS
   (Reuters/ESA/Big City Beats)

   Humanity needs the ISS to conquer deep space, according to the head of
   Russia's space agency, Dmitry Rogozin. The orbiting station should keep
   operating indefinitely with crews from all over the world, he added.

US strikes deal with Honduras on asylum-seekers 6h ago

   A group of mostly Honduran migrants moving through Mexico (Getty
   Images/AFP/P. Pardo)

   The US and Honduras have signed a deal that will allow Washington to
   send more asylum-seekers there. But critics say it's not safe to seek
   asylum in Honduras, as it's is among the world's most violent
   countries.

Former Danske Bank chief in Estonia found dead 8h ago

   Former boss of Danske Bank in Estonia, Aivar Rehe
   (picture-alliance/Postimees/Scanpix)

   Police have launched an investigation after finding the body of Aivar
   Rehe — the former head of Danske Bank in Estonia. It came as German
   police swooped on bank offices as part of a money-laundering probe.

How Russian media are reporting on the murder of a Chechen man in Berlin 17h
ago

   Moscow, Russia (picture-alliance/Russian Look/Global Look Press)

   In late August, a Chechen man was shot dead at a Berlin park. Western
   media reported that the suspect may have ties to Russian intelligence
   services — but Russia has gone on the offensive to discredit the
   claims.
   Bronze age baby bottles

Prehistoric 'baby bottles' unearthed in Germany

   Researchers have discovered ancient ceramic vessels in Bavaria that
   contained traces of animal milk used to feed babies.

