   Trump State Dept Official: No country is doing more for religious
   freedom than US. Ambassador Sam Brownback: Do you think China is
   better?
   Advertisement
   Rohingya refugees at a camp in Cox's Bazar, Bangladesh

Why does Asia have millions of stateless people?

   Millions of people in Asia are not citizens of any country, and they
   live without legal rights or protection. Although modern conflicts
   shape the problem, statelessness is rooted in Asia's colonial past.
   Halva in a bakery in Greece (DW/F. Schmitz)

Macedonia name dispute waged on store shelves

   While Greece-North Macedonia ties have improved, businesses continue to
   bicker over how to label their products.
   A Yemeni woman holds her baby in her arms (CARE/Jennifer Bose)

Empowering women in Yemen's civil war

   Yemen is ranked worst in the world for gender equality. Yet CARE
   women's activist Suha Basharen sees glimmers of hope.
